  "birth_year": 1818,
  "death_year": 1893,
  "wikipedia_extract": "Charles-François Gounod (UK:  GOO-noh, US:  goo-NOH, French: [ʃaʁl fʁɑ̃swa ɡuno]; 17 June 1818 – 18 October 1893) was a French composer. He wrote twelve operas, of which the most popular has always been Faust (1859); his Roméo et Juliette (1867) also remains in the international repertoire. He composed a large amount of church music, many songs, and popular short pieces including his \"Ave Maria\" (an elaboration of a Bach piece) and \"Funeral March of a Marionette\".",
